  "body": "I saw this last night while I was running the beacon node, and while I was away, the beacon node stopped syncing when I ran out of disk space, and then when I hit Ctrl+C, it spit this out:\r\n\r\n```\r\n(node:28161) UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: Error: ENOSPC: no space left on device, write\r\n    at Object.writeSync (fs.js:589:3)\r\n    at writeFileSync (fs.js:1258:26)\r\n    at Map.saveToFile (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar-cli/src/network/fileEnr.ts:41:5)\r\n    at Map.set (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar-cli/src/network/fileEnr.ts:46:10)\r\n    at MetadataController.set attnets [as attnets] (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/network/metadata/metadata.ts:55:16)\r\n    at InteropSubnetsJoiningTask.cleanUpCurrentSubscriptions (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/tasks/tasks/interopSubnetsJoiningTask.ts:118:5)\r\n    at InteropSubnetsJoiningTask.stop (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/tasks/tasks/interopSubnetsJoiningTask.ts:51:17)\r\n    at TasksService.stop (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/tasks/index.ts:66:35)\r\n    at BeaconNode.stop (/home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/node/nodejs.ts:161:23)\r\n    at /home/seraph/work/ChainSafe/lodestar/packages/lodestar-cli/src/cmds/beacon/handler.ts:53:29\r\n(node:28161) UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: Unhandled promise rejection. This error originated either by throwing inside of an async function without a catch block, or by rejecting a promise which was not handled with .catch(). (rejection id: 1319)\r\n ```\r\n\r\nIt's an edge case and is something that is maybe hard to test for, but it would probably be good to handle the error and let the user know more kindly, imo.",
